                <h5 class="subheading">No Claim Bonus (NCB): Your Reward for Safe Riding</h5>
                <p>The <span class="font-weight-700">No Claim Bonus (NCB)</span> is a reward mechanism that insurers offer to policyholders for not raising any claims during the policy period. It is offered as a discount on the <span class="font-weight-700">Own Damage</span> portion of the premium upon renewal. This benefit is transferable when switching insurers or even when buying a new bike, provided the person sells the old one and buys a new one within a certain time frame.</p>
                <p>The NCB accumulates incrementally, rewarding long periods of claim-free riding. Once the maximum is reached, it can lead to significant savings on the renewal premium. </p>
